    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:'gg sans', 'Noto Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><em>An elegant, keen-edged blade that rests within a thoughtfully crafted Gloamwell darkwood cane. The pommel maintains the original bat-like talons resting around a deep red ruby gem in the center, with a slightly longer handle portion for easier manipulation. When drawn, the blade emits a palpable aura of shadow around the wielder, and the subtle hint of terror and inevitability when brandished against a foe. Woe be upon the Morneblade's foes, as he paves the way between light and darkness.</em></span></p><hr /><p>Schemering is a +3 major striking quickstrike greater astral keen cold iron sword cane. It has the following benefits when invested:</p><ul><li><p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">f </span><strong>Haunting Presence </strong>(Emotion) On a critical hit with this weapon, you may attempt to Demoralize your opponent as a free action.</p></li><li><p><strong>Shadow's ClingÂ </strong>Shadows seem to wrap and collect around your form. As long as you're in dim light or darkness, you can attempt a Stealth check to hide, even if you aren't concealed against a creature. In addition, you gain the @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.SE0fbgBj7atuukdv]{Cloak of Shadow} focus spell.</p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'gg sans', 'Noto Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><strong>Fated Duel</strong> When you've used your Exploit Vulnerability on a target, you suffer less penalties for repeated strikes. Your multiple attack penalty for attacks against targets with Exploit Vulnerability is -3 (-2 for an agile weapon) on your second attack of the turn instead of -5, and -6 (-4 with an agile weapon) on your third or subsequent attack of the turn, instead of -10.</span></p></li></ul>",
